n)|caps4   = 54 |goals4  = 0\n|nationalyears1    = 2008\u20132009 |nationalteam1  = [[Germany national under-16 football team|Germany U16]]|nationalcaps1  = 3 |nationalgoals1  = 0 \n|nationalyears2    = 2009      |nationalteam2  = [[Germany national under-17 football team|Germany U17]]|nationalcaps2  = 1 |nationalgoals2  = 0 \n|nationalyears3    = 2010      |nationalteam3  = [[Germany national under-18 football team|Germany U18]]|nationalcaps3  = 1 |nationalgoals3  = 0 \n|nationalyears4    = 2011      |nationalteam4  = [[Germany national under-19 football team|Germany U19]]|nationalcaps4  = 1 |nationalgoals4  = 0 \n|nationalyears5    = 2012      |nationalteam5  = [[Germany national under-20 football team|Germany U20]]|nationalcaps5  = 1 |nationalgoals5  = 0 \n|nationalyears6    = 2014      |nationalteam6  = [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]]|nationalcaps6  = 1 |nationalgoals6  = 0  \n|club-update       = 7 March 2020\n|nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Loris Sven Karius''' (born 22 June 1993) is a German professional footballer who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[S\u00fcper Lig]] club [[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]],<ref name=\"Liverpool FC\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/313594-loris-karius-besiktas-loan|title=Loris Karius joins Besiktas on two-year loan|work=Liverpool FC|access-date=2018-08-25}}</ref> on loan from [[Premier League]] club [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]. He represented Germany at [[Germany national youth football team|youth level]].\n\nBorn in [[Biberach an der Riss|Biberach]], Karius began his career with [[VfB Stuttgart|Stuttgart]] before moving to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in 2009. After two years in Manchester City's youth system, he returned to Germany with [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]]. He established himself as first-choice goalkeeper for the [[Bundesliga]] side before transferring to Liverpool in 2016 for a fee of \u00a34.75&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/05/24/liverpool-sign-475m-goalkeeper-loris-karius-from-mainz/|title=Liverpool sign \u00a34.75m goalkeeper Loris Karius from Mainz|last=Bascombe|first=Chris|date=2016-05-24|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-06-04|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nKarius was born in [[Biberach an der Riss|Biberach]], Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg on 22 June 1993 to Christine and Harald Karius.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.schwaebische.de/home_artikel,-_arid,2795603.html|title=15-J\u00e4hriger Biberacher h\u00e4lt k\u00fcnftig Robinhos Sch\u00fcsse|author=Staff writer(s)|website=Schw\u00e4bische Zeitung das Onlineportal|language=German|date=8 May 2008|accessdate=7 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617015620/https://www.schwaebische.de/home_artikel,-_arid,2795603.html|archive-date=17 June 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> Harald intended for his son to become a [[motocross]] rider, but Loris' grandfather, Karl, encouraged him to focus on football.<ref name=goalinterview>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1862/premier-league/2016/11/09/29350962/introducing-loris-karius-how-the-goalkeeper-kicked-past-his|title=Introducing Loris Karius: How the goalkeeper kicked past his struggles to become Liverpool\u2019s No.1|first=Melissa|last=Reddy|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=10 November 2016|accessdate=16 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nKarius attended [[Pestalozzi-Gymnasium Biberach]] until his move to England in 2009 where he was then privately tutored.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.spox.com/de/sport/fussball/nachwuchs/1103/Artikel/loris-karius-vfb-stuttgart-manchester-city-jerome-boateng.html|title=Der Werdegang von Loris Karius bei Manchester City|author=Staff writer(s)|website=Spox|language=German|date=17 March 2011|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===Early career===\nKarius played for local team SG Mettenberg and [[SSV Ulm 1846]] before joining [[VfB Stuttgart]], where he rose through the youth ranks and appeared for the German under-16 national team against Macedonia in September 2008.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.schwaebische.de/mediathek_galid,205691_titel,-Fussballprofi-Loris-Karius-in-der-Heimat-_toid,157.html|title=Fu\u00dfballprofi Loris Karius in der Heimat|author=Staff writer(s)|website=Schw\u00e4bische Zeitung das Onlineportal|language=German|date=27 March 2016|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Manchester City===\n[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] invited Karius and his family to England after watching him in Germany's under-16 game against Azerbaijan, and completed his signing on 1 July 2009.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.espnfc.com/story/632981|title=Stuttgart hit out at City over young goalkeeper|author=Staff writer(s)|publisher=[[ESPN FC]]|date=26 March 2009|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> Karius played for the under-18 and the under-21 Manchester City teams, but failed to make a senior appearance during his time in Manchester.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/04/09/loris-karius-delighted-finally-get-game-former-club-man-city|title=Loris Karius delighted to finally get a game at former club Man City|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=7 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/sport/soccer/champions-league/loris-karius-out-to-prove-manchester-city-wrong-1.3455598|title=Loris Karius out to prove Manchester City wrong|newspaper=The Irish Times|accessdate=7 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Mainz 05===\n[[File:Loris-Karius-2015-07.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Karius with [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] in 2015]]\n\nManchester City loaned Karius to [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] in August 2011, where he played for Mainz 05's reserve team, [[1. FSV Mainz 05 II|Mainz 05 II]], in the [[Regionalliga]]. On 11 January 2012, the move was made permanent with Karius committing himself to a two-year deal with an option for a third year that would extend his contract to June 2015.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/563095/artikel_bis-2014_05-bindet-karius.html|title=Bis 2014: 05 bindet Karius|author=Staff writer(s)|magazine=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|kicker]]|language=German|date=11 January 2012|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nHe made his Mainz 05 debut on 1 December 2012 in a [[Bundesliga]] match against [[Hannover 96]] when he was substituted for [[Shawn Parker]] after goalkeeper [[Christian Wetklo]] had been sent off, which, aged 19 years, 5 months and 9 days old, made Karius the youngest goalkeeper ever to play in the Bundesliga.<ref name=goalinterview/><ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.goal.com/en/match/mainz-05-vs-hannover-96/1300903/lineups|title=Mainz 05 vs Hannover 96 Match Report|author=Staff writer(s)|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=1 December 2012|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> He made no further appearances in the 2012\u201313 season, but established himself as first-choice goalkeeper in the 2013\u201314 season and on 12 January 2015 signed a three-year contract extension.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.bundesliga.de/de/liga/news/loris-karius-verlaengert-bei-mainz-05.jsp|title=Loris Karius verl\u00e4ngert beim 1. FSV Mainz 05|author=Staff writer(s)|publisher=[[Bundesliga]]|language=German|date=12 January 2015|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/sport/football/419780/CONFIRMED-Arsenal-target-Loris-Karius-pens-contract-2018 |title=Arsenal target Loris Karius pens contract until 2018|first=Alex|last=Harris|newspaper=[[Daily Star (British newspaper)|Daily Star]]|date=12 January 2015|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nKarius was ever-present in the [[2015\u201316 1. FSV Mainz 05 season|2015\u201316 season]], keeping nine clean sheets, saving two penalties and being voted the second-best goalkeeper in the league in a poll of 235 fellow Bundesliga players, ranking behind only [[Manuel Neuer]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblmd32-bundesliga-your-team-of-the-season-goalkeepers.jsp|title=Team of the Season: Neuer sweeps the board in goalkeeper vote|author=Staff writer(s)|publisher=[[Bundesliga]]|date=6 May 2016|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/liverpool-bound-loris-karius-voted-11376318|title=Liverpool-bound Loris Karius voted second-best Bundesliga goalkeeper|first=Kristian|last=Walsh|newspaper=[[Liverpool Echo]]|date=24 May 2016|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Liverpool===\n[[File:Liver-SM 2017 (5) (Loris Karius).jpg|thumb|130px|Karius lining up for [[Liverpool F.C|Liverpool]] in 2017]]\n\nOn 24 May 2016, Karius signed with [[Liverpool F.C|Liverpool]] for a fee of \u00a34.75&nbsp;million on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/222991-liverpool-agree-deal-to-sign-loris-karius |title=Liverpool agree deal to sign Loris Karius |date=24 May 2016 |first=James |last=Carroll |publisher=[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool Football Club]] |accessdate=24 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/loris-karius-signs-liverpool-goalkeeper-transfer-news-a7046946.html|title=Mainz goalkeeper completes \u00a34.7million move after release clause activated|first=Simon|last=Hughes|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|date=24 May 2016|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> He was given the number 1 jersey.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/222989-liverpool-confirm-loris-karius-squad-number |title=Liverpool confirm Loris Karius squad number |date=24 May 2016 |first=James |last=Carroll |publisher=[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool Football Club]] |accessdate=24 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== 2016\u201317 season ====\nHe made his debut in a 3\u20130 [[EFL Cup]] win over [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] on 20 September 2016.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37346111|title=Derby 0\u20133 Liverpool |author=Staff writer(s)|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=20 September 2016|accessdate=21 September 2016}}</ref> He played his first [[Premier League]] match against [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]], which ended in a 5\u20131 victory for the Reds, on 24 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37393500 |title=Liverpool 5\u20131 Hull City |date=24 September 2016 |first=Phil|last=Dawkes|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> He kept his first Premier League [[Shutout|clean sheet]] on 17 October in a 0\u20130 draw with rivals [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/liverpool-loris-karius-de-gea-9072543|title=Liverpool keeper Loris Karius inspired by David De Gea and insists it will take time to produce at a high level|last=Maddock|first=David|date=18 October 2016|accessdate=24 October 2016|website=[[Daily Mirror]]}}</ref> On 24 October 2016, [[J\u00fcrgen Klopp]] confirmed that Karius was Liverpool's first-choice goalkeeper, ahead of [[Simon Mignolet]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/fa-league-cups/liverpool-news-jurgen-klopp-simon-mignolet-efl-cup-vs-spurs-a7378771.html |title=Liverpool news: Jurgen Klopp confirms Simon Mignolet is no longer No 1 as Liverpool prepare for EFL Cup clash |date=24 October 2016 |author=Staff writer(s) |newspaper=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> After two sub-par performances in early December, which included spilling [[Lewis Cook (footballer, born 1997)|Lewis Cook]]'s tame shot into the path of [[Nathan Ak\u00e9]] to tap home into an empty net to give Bournemouth a 4\u20133 win, Karius was dropped from the starting eleven. Regarding this decision, Klopp stated he wanted to take Karius \"out the firing line,\" and that \"Karius is a young goalkeeper. He will bounce back.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Liverpool boss Jurgen Klopp backs keeper for future success|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38324774|author=Staff writer(s)|accessdate=15 December 2016|work=BBC Sport|date=14 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== 2017\u201318 season ====\nIn the 2018 Champions League quarter-final 2nd leg at [[Manchester City]], with the aggregate scoreline at 3\u20131 to Liverpool Karius was involved in a controversial incident when he failed to clear a cross into the penalty area, punching the ball downward which ricocheted off teammate James Milner and into the path of Man City striker [[Gabriel Jesus]] who scored, only for the linesman to incorrectly give offside.<ref>{{cite news |title=Manchester City 1\u20132 (agg. 1\u20135) Liverpool: Mo Salah and Roberto Firmino stun Blues to advance to Champions League semi-finals \u2013 5 talking points |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/match-reports/manchester-city-1-2-agg-12338906 |access-date=12 July 2018 |newspaper=[[The Daily Mirror]] |last=Rathborn |first=Jack |date=10 April 2018}}</ref> In the Champions League semi-final home leg against [[AS Roma]], with the scoreline at 0\u20130, Karius let [[Aleksandar Kolarov]]'s shot go through his hands with the ball then hitting the crossbar, before Liverpool went on to win 5\u20132.<ref>{{cite news |title=Liverpool 5\u20132 Roma: Win unlike any football I've seen before \u2013 Lawrenson |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43888382 |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=25 April 2018 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |access-date=13 July 2018 |last=Lawrenson |first=Mark}}</ref> In the away game in Rome, Karius was involved in controversy when he came rushing out of his goal and brought down [[Edin Dzeko]] inside the penalty area, but instead of a penalty and red card the linesman gave offside in what ''The Telegraph'' called \u201can extremely tight call\u201d.<ref name=\"Telegraph\"/> Minutes later Karius parried a Roma shot into the path of Dzeko who made the scoreline 2\u20131 to Roma, before the game finished 4\u20132 to Roma and 7\u20136 to Liverpool on aggregate.<ref name=\"Telegraph\">{{cite news |title=Liverpool ride their luck in Rome but survive to reach eighth European Cup final |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/05/02/roma-vs-liverpool-champions-league-live-score-updates/ |access-date=12 July 2018 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |last=Burt |first=Jason |date=3 May 2018 |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group Limited]]}}</ref>\n\nKarius started for Liverpool against [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] in the [[2018 UEFA Champions League Final]] which Liverpool lost 3\u20131.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44258022|title=Real Madrid 3\u20131 Liverpool|date=2018-05-26|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-07-06|language=en-GB}}</ref> He was deemed at fault for two of the goals, the first and third; the first after his throw was blocked by [[Karim Benzema]] and deflected into the net, and the second after he mishandled [[Gareth Bale]]'s 40-yard strike.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/liverpool-stand-loris-karius-despite-14711508 |title=Liverpool will stand by Loris Karius despite Champions League horror show |newspaper=Liverpool Echo |author=Ian Doyle |date=27 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter the match, he wept and tearfully apologised to Liverpool fans who remained in the stands.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/05/26/loris-karius-gives-tearful-apology-liverpool-fans-mistakes-real-madrid-7580859/ |title=Loris Karius gives tearful apology to Liverpool fans after mistakes against Real Madrid |publisher=Metro |author=Chris Dawie |date=26 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref> He also stated that his mistakes \"lost the team the final\".<ref>{{cite news |date=26 May 2018 |title=Loris Karius apologises to Liverpool for Champions League horror show: 'my mistakes lost us the final' |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/loris-karius-liverpool-champions-league-mistakes-real-madrid-final-mohamed-salah-sergio-ramos-a8371136.html |work=The Independent |accessdate=26 May 2018}}</ref> After the match, Karius received online [[death threats]], mainly on [[Twitter]], which prompted [[Merseyside Police]] to launch an investigation.<ref>{{cite news |date=26 May 2018 |title=Liverpool goalkeeper Loris Karius sent death threats by fans after howlers during Champions League final |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/liverpool-goalkeeper-loris-karius-sent-death-threats-by-fans-after-howlers-during-champions-league-a3849211.html |publisher=Standard.co.uk |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=26 May 2018 |title=Loris Karius: Liverpool goalkeeper receives death threats after howlers|url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/loris-karius-liverpool-death-threats/|publisher=The South African |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref> Five days later, Karius underwent an examination at [[Massachusetts General Hospital]]. Medics concluded he had suffered a concussion from an elbow to his head, reportedly from [[Sergio Ramos]] just minutes before his first mistake. Doctors, however, did not pinpoint the exact moment he was concussed. According to doctor [[Ross Zafonte]], it was possible the concussion affected his performance.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zafonte |first1=Ross |last2=Herget |first2=Lenore |title=Statement regarding Loris Karius From Dr. Ross Zafonte and Lenore Herget, PT, DPT |url=https://www.massgeneral.org/News/newsarticle.aspx?id=6792 |publisher=[[Massachusetts General Hospital]] |accessdate=4 June 2018 |date=4 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Loris Karius: Liverpool keeper concussed during Champions League final \u2013 doctors |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44363648 |accessdate=4 June 2018 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=4 June 2018}}</ref> Later, on 6 July, at the start of pre season, Klopp stated that Karius was \"100% influenced by his concussion\", leading to his errors, with Klopp saying \"We don't use it as an excuse, we use it as an explanation. For me, it's 100% the explanation [for his performance]. He was influenced by that knock \u2013 that is 100%\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/jurgen-klopp-says-loris-karius-12862355|title=Klopp opens up on Karius Champions League final concussion for the first time|last=Jones|first=Mark|date=2018-07-06|work=mirror|access-date=2018-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44735514|title=Loris Karius: Liverpool keeper influenced by Champions League final concussion \u2013 Jurgen Klopp|date=2018-07-06|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-07-06|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/306090-jurgen-klopp-loris-karius-concussion|title=J\u00fcrgen Klopp speaks on Loris Karius concussion|work=Liverpool FC|access-date=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n\n==== 2018\u201319 season ====\nIn July 2018, Liverpool broke the world transfer fee record for a goalkeeper when they signed [[Alisson (footballer, born 1992)|Alisson]] for an initial fee of \u20ac62.5 million (\u00a356m), which could rise to \u20ac72 million (\u00a366.8 million) with performance-based bonuses, and his signing relegated Karius to a back up.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/liverpool-confirm-signing-alisson-becker-14930903 |title=Liverpool confirm signing of Alisson Becker in world record deal |author=Pearce, James |newspaper=Liverpool Echo |date=19 July 2018 |access-date=1 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180720022616/https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/liverpool-confirm-signing-alisson-becker-14930903 |archive-date=20 July 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==== Loan to Be\u015fikta\u015f ====\nOn 25 August 2018, Karius joined Turkish club [[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]] on a two-year loan move.<ref name=\"Liverpool FC\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45311332|title=Loris Karius: Liverpool goalkeeper joins Turkey's Besiktas on loan|date=2018-08-25|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-08-25|language=en-GB}}</ref> Karius put in some great performances for Besiktas in his first season at the Turkish club. He earned man of the match performances and he kept many clean sheets. His man of the match performance against Alanyaspor in a league match, particularly stands out. He made several world class saves against Alanyaspor and he kept a clean sheet which prevented Besiktas from losing.<ref>{{https://turkish-football.com/the-king-man-of-the-hour-big-boy-saves-fans-respond-to-liverpool-loanee-loris-karius-man-of-the-match-display-for-besiktas/}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, he sought legal action against Be\u015fikta\u015f for back payment of four months' wages which he alleged the club had failed to pay him.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/news/liverpool-keeper-karius-taking-legal-action-against-loan/11wscmjtq06n41348k9h1cwqhi|title=Liverpool keeper Karius taking legal action against loan club Besiktas over unpaid wages|publisher=Goal|date=12 March 2019|accessdate=13 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nKarius represented Germany at all youth levels from under-16 onward, but his appearances were limited due to competition from [[Manuel Neuer]], [[Timo Horn]], [[Bernd Leno]], [[Kevin Trapp]], [[Oliver Baumann]], [[Ralf Fahrmann]], [[Sven Ulreich]] and [[Marc-Andr\u00e9 ter Stegen]].{{citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 7 March 2020}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|National Cup{{efn|Includes [[DFB-Pokal]] and [[FA Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|League Cup{{efn|Includes [[EFL Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|Europe\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[1. FSV Mainz 05 II|Mainz 05 II]]\n|[[2011\u201312 Regionalliga#Regionalliga West|2011\u201312]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|[[Regionalliga West]]\n|18||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||18||0\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Regionalliga#Regionalliga S\u00fcdwest|2012\u201313]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|[[Regionalliga S\u00fcdwest]]\n|6||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||6||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Regionalliga#Regionalliga S\u00fcdwest|2013\u201314]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|Regionalliga S\u00fcdwest\n|3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||3||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!27||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||27||0\n|-\n|rowspan=6|[[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]]\n|[[2011\u201312 1. FSV Mainz 05 season|2011\u201312]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|[[Bundesliga]]\n|0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 1. FSV Mainz 05 season|2012\u201313]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|Bundesliga\n|1||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Bundesliga|2013\u201314]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|Bundesliga\n|23||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||23||0\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 1. FSV Mainz 05 season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|Bundesliga\n|33||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||2{{efn|name=UEL|Appearances in [[UEFA Europa League]]}}||0||36||0\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 1. FSV Mainz 05 season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|Bundesliga\n|34||0||2||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||36||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!91||0||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||2||0||96||0\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n|[[2016\u201317 Liverpool F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=sb1617>{{soccerbase season|63894|2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Premier League]]\n|10||0||3||0||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||16||0\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Liverpool F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=sb1718>{{soccerbase season|63894|2017|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|19||0||1||0||0||0||13{{efn|Appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]]}}||0||33||0\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Liverpool F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=sb1819>{{soccerbase season|63894|2018|accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||0||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!29||0||4||0||3||0||13||0||49||0\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]] (loan)\n|[[2018\u201319 Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=Soccerway>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/loris--karius/205201/ |title=L. Karius |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref>\n|[[S\u00fcper Lig]]\n|30||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||5{{efn|name=UEL}}||0||35||0\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K. season|2019\u201320]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|[[S\u00fcper Lig]]\n|24||0||2||0||colspan=2|\u2014||5{{efn|name=UEL}}||0||31||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!54||0||2||0||0||0||10||0||66||0\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!201||0||9||0||3||0||25||0||238||0\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Liverpool'''\n*[[UEFA Champions League]] runner-up: [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44258022 |title=Real Madrid 3\u20131 Liverpool |first=Phil |last=McNulty |work=BBC Sport |date=26 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.liverpoolfc.com/team/first-team/player/loris-karius Liverpool F.C. profile]\n*{{Soccerbase|63894}}\n\n<!-- {{Liverpool F.C. squad}} -->\n{{Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karius, Loris}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Biberach an der Riss]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Manchester City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:1. FSV Mainz 05 II players]]\n[[Category:1. FSV Mainz 05 players]]\n[[Category:Liverpool F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K. footballers]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:Germany youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Germany under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:German expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:German expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:German expatriate sportspeople in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Turkey]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|German footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{redirect|Karius|the Australian explorer|Charles Karius|the German music conductor|Wolfgang Karius|the Norwegian children's novel|Karius and Bactus}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = Loris Karius\n|image       = Loris Karius.jpg\n|image_size  = 200\n|caption     = Karius playing for [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in the [[2018 UEFA Champions League Final]]\n|fullname    = Loris Sven Karius<ref>{{cite web |title=Squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/465277 |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2017 |accessdate=9 September 2017}}</ref>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1993|6|22|df=y}} \n|birth_place = [[Biberach an der Riss]], Germany\n|height      = 1.89m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/19600/Loris-Karius/overview |title=Loris Karius: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref>\n|position    = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n|currentclub = [[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]]<br>(on loan from [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]])\n|clubnumber  = 1\n|youthyears1 = 1998\u20132000\n|youthclubs1 = FV Biberach\n|youthyears2 = 2000\u20132001\n|youthclubs2 = SG Mettenberg\n|youthyears3 = 2001\u20132005\n|youthclubs3 = [[SSV Ulm 1846]]\n|youthyears4 = 2005\u20132009\n|youthclubs4 = [[VfB Stuttgart]]\n|youthyears5 = 2009\u20132011\n|youthclubs5 = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n|years1      = 2011\u20132013 |clubs1      = [[1. FSV Mainz 05 II|Mainz 05 II]] |caps1   = 27 |goals1  = 0\n|years2      = 2012\u20132016 |clubs2      = [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]]       |caps2   = 91 |goals2  = 0\n|years3      = 2016\u2013     |clubs3      = [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]       |caps3   = 29 |goals3  = 0\n|years4      = 2018\u2013     |clubs4      = \u2192 [[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]] (loan)|caps4   = 54 |goals4  = 0\n|nationalyears1    = 2008\u20132009 |nationalteam1  = [[Germany national under-16 football team|Germany U16]]|nationalcaps1  = 3 |nationalgoals1  = 0 \n|nationalyears2    = 2009      |nationalteam2  = [[Germany national under-17 football team|Germany U17]]|nationalcaps2  = 1 |nationalgoals2  = 0 \n|nationalyears3    = 2010      |nationalteam3  = [[Germany national under-18 football team|Germany U18]]|nationalcaps3  = 1 |nationalgoals3  = 0 \n|nationalyears4    = 2011      |nationalteam4  = [[Germany national under-19 football team|Germany U19]]|nationalcaps4  = 1 |nationalgoals4  = 0 \n|nationalyears5    = 2012      |nationalteam5  = [[Germany national under-20 football team|Germany U20]]|nationalcaps5  = 1 |nationalgoals5  = 0 \n|nationalyears6    = 2014      |nationalteam6  = [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]]|nationalcaps6  = 1 |nationalgoals6  = 0  \n|club-update       = 7 March 2020\n|nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Loris Sven Karius''' (born 22 June 1993) is a German professional footballer who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[S\u00fcper Lig]] club [[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]],<ref name=\"Liverpool FC\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/313594-loris-karius-besiktas-loan|title=Loris Karius joins Besiktas on two-year loan|work=Liverpool FC|access-date=2018-08-25}}</ref> on loan from [[Premier League]] club [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]. He represented Germany at [[Germany national youth football team|youth level]].\n\nBorn in [[Biberach an der Riss|Biberach]], Karius began his career with [[VfB Stuttgart|Stuttgart]] before moving to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in 2009. After two years in Manchester City's youth system, he returned to Germany with [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]]. He established himself as first-choice goalkeeper for the [[Bundesliga]] side before transferring to Liverpool in 2016 for a fee of \u00a34.75&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/05/24/liverpool-sign-475m-goalkeeper-loris-karius-from-mainz/|title=Liverpool sign \u00a34.75m goalkeeper Loris Karius from Mainz|last=Bascombe|first=Chris|date=2016-05-24|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-06-04|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nKarius was born in [[Biberach an der Riss|Biberach]], Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg on 22 June 1993 to Christine and Harald Karius.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.schwaebische.de/home_artikel,-_arid,2795603.html|title=15-J\u00e4hriger Biberacher h\u00e4lt k\u00fcnftig Robinhos Sch\u00fcsse|author=Staff writer(s)|website=Schw\u00e4bische Zeitung das Onlineportal|language=German|date=8 May 2008|accessdate=7 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617015620/https://www.schwaebische.de/home_artikel,-_arid,2795603.html|archive-date=17 June 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> Harald intended for his son to become a [[motocross]] rider, but Loris' grandfather, Karl, encouraged him to focus on football.<ref name=goalinterview>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1862/premier-league/2016/11/09/29350962/introducing-loris-karius-how-the-goalkeeper-kicked-past-his|title=Introducing Loris Karius: How the goalkeeper kicked past his struggles to become Liverpool\u2019s No.1|first=Melissa|last=Reddy|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=10 November 2016|accessdate=16 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nKarius attended [[Pestalozzi-Gymnasium Biberach]] until his move to England in 2009 where he was then privately tutored.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.spox.com/de/sport/fussball/nachwuchs/1103/Artikel/loris-karius-vfb-stuttgart-manchester-city-jerome-boateng.html|title=Der Werdegang von Loris Karius bei Manchester City|author=Staff writer(s)|website=Spox|language=German|date=17 March 2011|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===Early career===\nKarius played for local team SG Mettenberg and [[SSV Ulm 1846]] before joining [[VfB Stuttgart]], where he rose through the youth ranks and appeared for the German under-16 national team against Macedonia in September 2008.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.schwaebische.de/mediathek_galid,205691_titel,-Fussballprofi-Loris-Karius-in-der-Heimat-_toid,157.html|title=Fu\u00dfballprofi Loris Karius in der Heimat|author=Staff writer(s)|website=Schw\u00e4bische Zeitung das Onlineportal|language=German|date=27 March 2016|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Manchester City===\n[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] invited Karius and his family to England after watching him in Germany's under-16 game against Azerbaijan, and completed his signing on 1 July 2009.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.espnfc.com/story/632981|title=Stuttgart hit out at City over young goalkeeper|author=Staff writer(s)|publisher=[[ESPN FC]]|date=26 March 2009|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> Karius played for the under-18 and the under-21 Manchester City teams, but failed to make a senior appearance during his time in Manchester.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/04/09/loris-karius-delighted-finally-get-game-former-club-man-city|title=Loris Karius delighted to finally get a game at former club Man City|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=7 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/sport/soccer/champions-league/loris-karius-out-to-prove-manchester-city-wrong-1.3455598|title=Loris Karius out to prove Manchester City wrong|newspaper=The Irish Times|accessdate=7 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Mainz 05===\n[[File:Loris-Karius-2015-07.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Karius with [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] in 2015]]\n\nManchester City loaned Karius to [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] in August 2011, where he played for Mainz 05's reserve team, [[1. FSV Mainz 05 II|Mainz 05 II]], in the [[Regionalliga]]. On 11 January 2012, the move was made permanent with Karius committing himself to a two-year deal with an option for a third year that would extend his contract to June 2015.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/563095/artikel_bis-2014_05-bindet-karius.html|title=Bis 2014: 05 bindet Karius|author=Staff writer(s)|magazine=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|kicker]]|language=German|date=11 January 2012|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nHe made his Mainz 05 debut on 1 December 2012 in a [[Bundesliga]] match against [[Hannover 96]] when he was substituted for [[Shawn Parker]] after goalkeeper [[Christian Wetklo]] had been sent off, which, aged 19 years, 5 months and 9 days old, made Karius the youngest goalkeeper ever to play in the Bundesliga.<ref name=goalinterview/><ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.goal.com/en/match/mainz-05-vs-hannover-96/1300903/lineups|title=Mainz 05 vs Hannover 96 Match Report|author=Staff writer(s)|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=1 December 2012|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> He made no further appearances in the 2012\u201313 season, but established himself as first-choice goalkeeper in the 2013\u201314 season and on 12 January 2015 signed a three-year contract extension.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.bundesliga.de/de/liga/news/loris-karius-verlaengert-bei-mainz-05.jsp|title=Loris Karius verl\u00e4ngert beim 1. FSV Mainz 05|author=Staff writer(s)|publisher=[[Bundesliga]]|language=German|date=12 January 2015|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/sport/football/419780/CONFIRMED-Arsenal-target-Loris-Karius-pens-contract-2018 |title=Arsenal target Loris Karius pens contract until 2018|first=Alex|last=Harris|newspaper=[[Daily Star (British newspaper)|Daily Star]]|date=12 January 2015|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nKarius was ever-present in the [[2015\u201316 1. FSV Mainz 05 season|2015\u201316 season]], keeping nine clean sheets, saving two penalties and being voted the second-best goalkeeper in the league in a poll of 235 fellow Bundesliga players, ranking behind only [[Manuel Neuer]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblmd32-bundesliga-your-team-of-the-season-goalkeepers.jsp|title=Team of the Season: Neuer sweeps the board in goalkeeper vote|author=Staff writer(s)|publisher=[[Bundesliga]]|date=6 May 2016|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/liverpool-bound-loris-karius-voted-11376318|title=Liverpool-bound Loris Karius voted second-best Bundesliga goalkeeper|first=Kristian|last=Walsh|newspaper=[[Liverpool Echo]]|date=24 May 2016|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Liverpool===\n[[File:Liver-SM 2017 (5) (Loris Karius).jpg|thumb|130px|Karius lining up for [[Liverpool F.C|Liverpool]] in 2017]]\n\nOn 24 May 2016, Karius signed with [[Liverpool F.C|Liverpool]] for a fee of \u00a34.75&nbsp;million on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/222991-liverpool-agree-deal-to-sign-loris-karius |title=Liverpool agree deal to sign Loris Karius |date=24 May 2016 |first=James |last=Carroll |publisher=[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool Football Club]] |accessdate=24 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/loris-karius-signs-liverpool-goalkeeper-transfer-news-a7046946.html|title=Mainz goalkeeper completes \u00a34.7million move after release clause activated|first=Simon|last=Hughes|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|date=24 May 2016|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> He was given the number 1 jersey.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/222989-liverpool-confirm-loris-karius-squad-number |title=Liverpool confirm Loris Karius squad number |date=24 May 2016 |first=James |last=Carroll |publisher=[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool Football Club]] |accessdate=24 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== 2016\u201317 season ====\nHe made his debut in a 3\u20130 [[EFL Cup]] win over [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] on 20 September 2016.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37346111|title=Derby 0\u20133 Liverpool |author=Staff writer(s)|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=20 September 2016|accessdate=21 September 2016}}</ref> He played his first [[Premier League]] match against [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]], which ended in a 5\u20131 victory for the Reds, on 24 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37393500 |title=Liverpool 5\u20131 Hull City |date=24 September 2016 |first=Phil|last=Dawkes|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> He kept his first Premier League [[Shutout|clean sheet]] on 17 October in a 0\u20130 draw with rivals [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/liverpool-loris-karius-de-gea-9072543|title=Liverpool keeper Loris Karius inspired by David De Gea and insists it will take time to produce at a high level|last=Maddock|first=David|date=18 October 2016|accessdate=24 October 2016|website=[[Daily Mirror]]}}</ref> On 24 October 2016, [[J\u00fcrgen Klopp]] confirmed that Karius was Liverpool's first-choice goalkeeper, ahead of [[Simon Mignolet]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/fa-league-cups/liverpool-news-jurgen-klopp-simon-mignolet-efl-cup-vs-spurs-a7378771.html |title=Liverpool news: Jurgen Klopp confirms Simon Mignolet is no longer No 1 as Liverpool prepare for EFL Cup clash |date=24 October 2016 |author=Staff writer(s) |newspaper=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref> After two sub-par performances in early December, which included spilling [[Lewis Cook (footballer, born 1997)|Lewis Cook]]'s tame shot into the path of [[Nathan Ak\u00e9]] to tap home into an empty net to give Bournemouth a 4\u20133 win, Karius was dropped from the starting eleven. Regarding this decision, Klopp stated he wanted to take Karius \"out the firing line,\" and that \"Karius is a young goalkeeper. He will bounce back.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Liverpool boss Jurgen Klopp backs keeper for future success|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38324774|author=Staff writer(s)|accessdate=15 December 2016|work=BBC Sport|date=14 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== 2017\u201318 season ====\nIn the 2018 Champions League quarter-final 2nd leg at [[Manchester City]], with the aggregate scoreline at 3\u20131 to Liverpool Karius was involved in a controversial incident when he failed to clear a cross into the penalty area, punching the ball downward which ricocheted off teammate James Milner and into the path of Man City striker [[Gabriel Jesus]] who scored, only for the linesman to incorrectly give offside.<ref>{{cite news |title=Manchester City 1\u20132 (agg. 1\u20135) Liverpool: Mo Salah and Roberto Firmino stun Blues to advance to Champions League semi-finals \u2013 5 talking points |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/match-reports/manchester-city-1-2-agg-12338906 |access-date=12 July 2018 |newspaper=[[The Daily Mirror]] |last=Rathborn |first=Jack |date=10 April 2018}}</ref> In the Champions League semi-final home leg against [[AS Roma]], with the scoreline at 0\u20130, Karius let [[Aleksandar Kolarov]]'s shot go through his hands with the ball then hitting the crossbar, before Liverpool went on to win 5\u20132.<ref>{{cite news |title=Liverpool 5\u20132 Roma: Win unlike any football I've seen before \u2013 Lawrenson |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43888382 |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=25 April 2018 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |access-date=13 July 2018 |last=Lawrenson |first=Mark}}</ref> In the away game in Rome, Karius was involved in controversy when he came rushing out of his goal and brought down [[Edin Dzeko]] inside the penalty area, but instead of a penalty and red card the linesman gave offside in what ''The Telegraph'' called \u201can extremely tight call\u201d.<ref name=\"Telegraph\"/> Minutes later Karius parried a Roma shot into the path of Dzeko who made the scoreline 2\u20131 to Roma, before the game finished 4\u20132 to Roma and 7\u20136 to Liverpool on aggregate.<ref name=\"Telegraph\">{{cite news |title=Liverpool ride their luck in Rome but survive to reach eighth European Cup final |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/05/02/roma-vs-liverpool-champions-league-live-score-updates/ |access-date=12 July 2018 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |last=Burt |first=Jason |date=3 May 2018 |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group Limited]]}}</ref>\n\nKarius started for Liverpool against [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] in the [[2018 UEFA Champions League Final]] which Liverpool lost 3\u20131.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44258022|title=Real Madrid 3\u20131 Liverpool|date=2018-05-26|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-07-06|language=en-GB}}</ref> He was deemed at fault for two of the goals, the first and third; the first after his throw was blocked by [[Karim Benzema]] and deflected into the net, and the second after he mishandled [[Gareth Bale]]'s 40-yard strike.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/liverpool-stand-loris-karius-despite-14711508 |title=Liverpool will stand by Loris Karius despite Champions League horror show |newspaper=Liverpool Echo |author=Ian Doyle |date=27 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter the match, he wept and tearfully apologised to Liverpool fans who remained in the stands.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/05/26/loris-karius-gives-tearful-apology-liverpool-fans-mistakes-real-madrid-7580859/ |title=Loris Karius gives tearful apology to Liverpool fans after mistakes against Real Madrid |publisher=Metro |author=Chris Dawie |date=26 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref> He also stated that his mistakes \"lost the team the final\".<ref>{{cite news |date=26 May 2018 |title=Loris Karius apologises to Liverpool for Champions League horror show: 'my mistakes lost us the final' |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/loris-karius-liverpool-champions-league-mistakes-real-madrid-final-mohamed-salah-sergio-ramos-a8371136.html |work=The Independent |accessdate=26 May 2018}}</ref> After the match, Karius received online [[death threats]], mainly on [[Twitter]], which prompted [[Merseyside Police]] to launch an investigation.<ref>{{cite news |date=26 May 2018 |title=Liverpool goalkeeper Loris Karius sent death threats by fans after howlers during Champions League final |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/liverpool-goalkeeper-loris-karius-sent-death-threats-by-fans-after-howlers-during-champions-league-a3849211.html |publisher=Standard.co.uk |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=26 May 2018 |title=Loris Karius: Liverpool goalkeeper receives death threats after howlers|url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/loris-karius-liverpool-death-threats/|publisher=The South African |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref> Five days later, Karius underwent an examination at [[Massachusetts General Hospital]]. Medics concluded he had suffered a concussion from an elbow to his head, reportedly from [[Sergio Ramos]] just minutes before his first mistake. Doctors, however, did not pinpoint the exact moment he was concussed. According to doctor [[Ross Zafonte]], it was possible the concussion affected his performance.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zafonte |first1=Ross |last2=Herget |first2=Lenore |title=Statement regarding Loris Karius From Dr. Ross Zafonte and Lenore Herget, PT, DPT |url=https://www.massgeneral.org/News/newsarticle.aspx?id=6792 |publisher=[[Massachusetts General Hospital]] |accessdate=4 June 2018 |date=4 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Loris Karius: Liverpool keeper concussed during Champions League final \u2013 doctors |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44363648 |accessdate=4 June 2018 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=4 June 2018}}</ref> Later, on 6 July, at the start of pre season, Klopp stated that Karius was \"100% influenced by his concussion\", leading to his errors, with Klopp saying \"We don't use it as an excuse, we use it as an explanation. For me, it's 100% the explanation [for his performance]. He was influenced by that knock \u2013 that is 100%\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/jurgen-klopp-says-loris-karius-12862355|title=Klopp opens up on Karius Champions League final concussion for the first time|last=Jones|first=Mark|date=2018-07-06|work=mirror|access-date=2018-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44735514|title=Loris Karius: Liverpool keeper influenced by Champions League final concussion \u2013 Jurgen Klopp|date=2018-07-06|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-07-06|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/306090-jurgen-klopp-loris-karius-concussion|title=J\u00fcrgen Klopp speaks on Loris Karius concussion|work=Liverpool FC|access-date=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n\n==== 2018\u201319 season ====\nIn July 2018, Liverpool broke the world transfer fee record for a goalkeeper when they signed [[Alisson (footballer, born 1992)|Alisson]] for an initial fee of \u20ac62.5 million (\u00a356m), which could rise to \u20ac72 million (\u00a366.8 million) with performance-based bonuses, and his signing relegated Karius to a back up.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/liverpool-confirm-signing-alisson-becker-14930903 |title=Liverpool confirm signing of Alisson Becker in world record deal |author=Pearce, James |newspaper=Liverpool Echo |date=19 July 2018 |access-date=1 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180720022616/https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/liverpool-confirm-signing-alisson-becker-14930903 |archive-date=20 July 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==== Loan to Be\u015fikta\u015f ====\nOn 25 August 2018, Karius joined Turkish club [[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]] on a two-year loan move.<ref name=\"Liverpool FC\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45311332|title=Loris Karius: Liverpool goalkeeper joins Turkey's Besiktas on loan|date=2018-08-25|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-08-25|language=en-GB}}</ref> Karius put in some great performances for Besiktas in his first season at the Turkish club. He earned man of the match performances and he kept many clean sheets. His man of the match performance against Alanyaspor in a league match, particularly stands out. He made several world class saves against Alanyaspor and he kept a clean sheet which prevented Besiktas from losing.<ref>{{https://turkish-football.com/the-king-man-of-the-hour-big-boy-saves-fans-respond-to-liverpool-loanee-loris-karius-man-of-the-match-display-for-besiktas/}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, he sought legal action against Be\u015fikta\u015f for back payment of four months' wages which he alleged the club had failed to pay him.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/news/liverpool-keeper-karius-taking-legal-action-against-loan/11wscmjtq06n41348k9h1cwqhi|title=Liverpool keeper Karius taking legal action against loan club Besiktas over unpaid wages|publisher=Goal|date=12 March 2019|accessdate=13 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nKarius represented Germany at all youth levels from under-16 onward, but his appearances were limited due to competition from [[Manuel Neuer]], [[Timo Horn]], [[Bernd Leno]], [[Kevin Trapp]], [[Oliver Baumann]], [[Ralf Fahrmann]], [[Sven Ulreich]] and [[Marc-Andr\u00e9 ter Stegen]].{{citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 7 March 2020}}\n\n{| 