ool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n|[[2016\u201317 Liverpool F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=sb1617>{{soccerbase season|63894|2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Premier League]]\n|10||0||3||0||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||16||0\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Liverpool F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=sb1718>{{soccerbase season|63894|2017|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|19||0||1||0||0||0||13{{efn|Appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]]}}||0||33||0\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Liverpool F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=sb1819>{{soccerbase season|63894|2018|accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||0||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!29||0||4||0||3||0||13||0||49||0\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]] (loan)\n|[[2018\u201319 Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=Soccerway>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/loris--karius/205201/ |title=L. Karius |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref>\n|[[S\u00fcper Lig]]\n|30||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||5{{efn|name=UEL}}||0||35||0\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K. season|2019\u201320]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|[[S\u00fcper Lig]]\n|24||0||2||0||colspan=2|\u2014||5{{efn|name=UEL}}||0||31||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!54||0||2||0||0||0||10||0||66||0\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!201||0||9||0||3||0||25||0||238||0\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Liverpool'''\n*[[UEFA Champions League]] runner-up: [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44258022 |title=Real Madrid 3\u20131 Liverpool |first=Phil |last=McNulty |work=BBC Sport |date=26 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.liverpoolfc.com/team/first-team/player/loris-karius Liverpool F.C. profile]\n*{{Soccerbase|63894}}\n\n<!-- {{Liverpool F.C. squad}} -->\n{{Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karius, Loris}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Biberach an der Riss]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Manchester City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:1. FSV Mainz 05 II players]]\n[[Category:1. FSV Mainz 05 players]]\n[[Category:Liverpool F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K. footballers]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:Germany youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Germany under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:German expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:German expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:German expatriate sportspeople in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Turkey]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:724d:c300:9123:58c7:f4b6:4386", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loris_Karius"}
{"title_page": "Jazzy B", "text_new": "{{For|the music producer and founder of [[Soul II Soul]]|Jazzie B}}\n{{EngvarB|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Jazzy B\n| image               = File:Bhangra Night Jazzy B!!!!!!.jpg\n| caption             = Jazzy Bains\n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          = Jaswinder Singh Fudu Bains\n| alias               = Jazzy B\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1975|4|1}}<ref>{{cite web=Latest News, Trending Topics, Top Stories, HD Videos & Photos, Live TV Channels, Lifestyle, Sports, Entertainment|website=In.com|accessdate=15 December 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_place         = [[Jalandhar]], [[Punjab, India|Punjab]], India\n| origin              = [[Surrey, British Columbia]], Canada\n| genre               = [[Bhangra (music)|Bhangra]], [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n| associated_acts     = [[Sukshinder Shinda]], [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]], Popsy The Music Machine, [[Aman Hayer]], [[Kuldeep Manak]], [[Gippy Grewal]], [[Garry Sandhu]], [[Snoop Dogg]], [[Mr. Capone-E]]\n| occupation          = Singer, actor\n| years_active        = 1993\u2013present \n| website ={{url|jazzyb.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Jaswinder Singh Fuda''' (born 1 April 1975), better known by his stage name '''Jazzy B''' is an Indian-Canadian Punjabi playback singer and songwriter.\n\n== Early life and career ==\nJazzy was born in [[Nawanshahr]], [[Punjab, India]]. When he was five years old, his family moved to [[Surrey, British Columbia|Surrey]], [[British Columbia]], Canada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailyhive.com/vancouver/canucks-jazzy-b-diwali-night|title=Bhangra superstar Jazzy B to perform at Canucks game next week {{!}} Offside|website=dailyhive.com|language=en|access-date=2019-10-26}}</ref> He is a big fan of the late singer [[Kuldeep Manak]].\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.darpanmagazine.com/2009/07/one-on-one-with-the-legendary-jazzy|title=One on One with the Legendary JAZZY B|publisher=Darpan Magazine|date=1 April 1975|accessdate=31 January 2012}}</ref>\nHis first album ''Gugiyan Da Jora'' was released in 1993. The rhythm was played by [[Sukhshinder Shinda]] who suggested that he move to England if he wanted a prominent career in [[Punjabi music]].<ref>http://www.bhangra.org/6-interesting-facts-about-jazzy-b/776801/</ref>\n\nJazzy has released 12 studio albums, and two religious ones. He has collaborated on many tracks.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/All-Jazzed-up/articleshow/29091271.cms|title=All Jazzed up!|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=22 November 2002|accessdate=18 February 2012|author=Singh, Harneet}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/How-ice-hockey-made-Jaswinder-into-Jazzy/articleshow/1339356087.cms|title=How ice hockey made Jaswinder into Jazzy|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=15 September 2001|accessdate=18 February 2012|author=Bhandari, Geetika Sasan}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2001/20011119/login/music.htm|title=Born in India, brought up in Canada \u2013 Oh! Keda?|work=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]|date=19 November 2001|accessdate=18 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2002/20021123/windows/zero.htm|title=The king of bhangra pop|work=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]|date=23 November 2002|accessdate=18 February 2012|author=Pal, Dharam}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2008/20080704/ttlife1.htm|title=More than just JAZZ|work=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]|date=4 July 2008|accessdate=18 February 2012|author=Khurana, Manpriya}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nJazzy is married to Hardeep Kaur and they have two children. He now resides in [[Birmingham]], [[England]].<ref>He is[http://www.last.fm/music/Panjabi+MC/+similar Similar artists to Panjabi MC \u2013 Discover music, videos, concerts, stats, & pictures at]. Last.fm (22 March 2012); retrieved 5 June 2012.</ref>\n\n==Film career==\nIn 2000 Jazzy made his film debut in ''[[Shaheed Udham Singh (film)|Shaheed Udham Singh]]''. In 2006 he appeared in [[Sunny Deol]]'s movie ''[[Teesri Aankh: The Hidden Camera]]'' with [[Amisha Patel]] in song Chug De Punjabi.\n\nIn 2012 he made a film as an actor with [[Punjabi people|Punjabi]] singer and actor [[Gippy Grewal]] and Miss India Universe 2008 [[Simran Kaur Mundi]]. The shooting of this film commenced in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]] in May 2012. \nHe made special appearance in [[Diljit Dosanjh]]'s [[Jatt & Juliet 2]] in 2013.\n<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=Irv9CfDWgkY</ref>\n\nIn 2014, he appeared in ''[[Romeo Ranjha]]''.\nIn a news story published in April, it was revealed that while doing stunts for [[Romeo Ranjha]], Jazzy underwent serious injuries wherein he even had \"near-death\" experience. He was quoted as saying, \"I literally left my body. I could feel everyone trying to resuscitate me. I remember my whole life flashing before my eyes, and surprisingly, I wasn't thinking about winning awards or anything like that. The only thing I cared about was that I wanted to live because I did not want to leave my family so soon.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Ballewood.in|title=When Jazzy B met with Death|url=http://ballewood.in/movies/news/jazzy-b-met-with-death|publisher=Ballewood.in|accessdate=3 April 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140405232204/http://ballewood.in/movies/news/jazzy-b-met-with-death|archivedate=5 April 2014}}</ref>\nIn 2014 he made a special appearance in [[Dharmendra]]'s and [[Gippy Grewal]]'s movie [[Double Di Trouble]].<ref>https://\nhttps://punjabimania.com/jazzy-b-does-a-cameo-in-double-di-trouble/</ref>\n\nIn 2015 he featured in title song \"Zalim Dilli\"of movie ''[[Dilliwali Zaalim Girlfriend]]''  with [[Hard Kaur]].<ref>https://www.india.com/buzz/zaalim-dilli-song-from-dilliwaali-zaalim-girlfriend-jazzy-b-and-hard-kaur-roll-out-a-club-mix-309896/</ref>\n\nIn 2020 he featured in song \"Gallan Kardi\" with [[Saif Ali Khan ]] for movie [[Jawaani Jaaneman]].<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=mSY1QrJd1f8</ref>\n\n==Work==\nFrom his music video \"Surma\" [[John Abraham]] started his modelling career in 2000.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DZpnJvwp6N8 |title=Surma' \u2013 John Abraham Jazzy B (Punjabi Album) HQ.flv |via=YouTube |date=21 October 2010 |accessdate=21 July 2012}}</ref>\nIn 2001 his song \"Oh Kehri\" from the album of same name featured [[Celina Jaitley]].<ref>https://m.timesofindia.com/city/How-ice-hockey-made-Jaswinder-into-Jazzy/articleshow/1339356087.cms</ref> [[Mahek Chahal]] featured in his songs and videos \"Jindey\" and \"Chak De Boli\".<ref>http://www.fashioncentral.in/people-parties/celebrity-birthdays/things-you-know-about-mahek-chahal/</ref> He is known for his song \"[[Dil Luteya]]\" with [[Apache Indian]] from his album ''[[Romeo (album)|Romeo]]''. [[Esha Gupta]] featured in his song \"Glassy\" from the album ''Rambo'' in 2008.<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=xxjJ8KjTjWU</ref> [[Surveen Chawla]] appeared in his song \"Naag 2\" in 2010.<ref>https://www.ghaintpunjab.com/navneet-dhillon-jazzy-b-naag-3/</ref>\n\nHe sung a song named \"Fukraa\" for [[Emraan Hashmi]] starrer movie [[Rush (2012 film)|Rush]] in 2012.<ref> https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=d6CAWVQdYrE</ref>\nIn 2013 he sung a song \"Jugni\" for [[Jimmy Sheirgill]], [[Irrfan Khan]], [[Soha Ali Khan]], and [[Mahi Gill]] starrer [[Saheb, Biwi Aur Gangster Returns]].<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=IiTfHLs_5gU</ref>\n\nIn 2014 [[Surveen Chawla]] once again appeared in his Duet song \"Mitran De Boot\".<ref>https://www.desiblitz.com/content/mitran-de-boot-jazzy-b-dr-zeus-and-kaur-b-smash</ref> In 2014 he also sung for movie [[Shaadi Ke Side Effects]] starring [[Farhan Akhtar]] and [[Vidya Balan]].<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=-YkW0G1Gcbk</ref>\n\nIn 2015 he worked with international rapper [[Snoop Dogg]] for the song \"Most Wanted\" which is featured in [[MTV]] [[India]].<ref>https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/punjabi/music/Out-now-Most-wanted-by-Jazzy-B-featuring-Snoop-Dogg-and-Mr-Capone-E/articleshow/49262261.cms</ref> His old song \"Sat Rangey\" played in the background of the [[Hollywood]] movie ''[[Deadpool (film)|Deadpool]]''  in 2016.<ref>https://www.tunefind.com/movie/deadpool-2016</ref> \nHe is the first South Asian entertainer to have his name added to the [[BC Entertainment Hall of Fame]] Star Walk in [[Vancouver]].<ref>https://www.ghaintpunjab.com/starwalk/</ref> \n\nIn 2016 he sung a song \"Love The Way You Dance\" for movie [[Tutak Tutak Tutiya]] starring [[Prabhu Deva]], [[Tamannaah]] and [[Sonu Sood]].<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=xvljBibGLm8 </ref>\n\nIn 2017 [[Bigg Boss]] ''[[Bigg Boss (Hindi season 10)|Season 10]]'' contestant [[Lopamudra Raut]] was featured in his song Crazy Ya from album ''[[Folk 'N' Funky 2]].''<ref>https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bigg-boss-season-10/bigg-boss-10-lopamudra-raut-jazzy-b-music-video-hot-photoshoot-watch-video-pics-4568890/</ref>\nIn 2019 he sung the song \"Ajj Singh Garjega\" for [[Akshay Kumar]]'s movie ''[[Kesari (film)|Kesari]]''.\n<ref>https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/kesari-song-ajj-singh-garjega-akshay-kumar-goes-behind-the-mic-to-tease-the-power-packed-track-watch-video/376393</ref>\n\nIn 2020 his song \"Jine Mera Dil Luteya\" recreated as \"Gaallan Kardi\" with [[Jyotica Tangri]] & [[Mumzy Stranger]] for [[Saif Ali Khan]], [[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]] & [[Alaya Furniturewala]] starrer [[Jawaani Jaaneman]].<ref>https://m.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/jawaani-jaaneman-song-gallan-kardi-saif-ali-khan-alaya-and-tabu-unearth-jazzy-b-and-his-chartbuster-for-a-dance-party/story-DWok446eKjYEn97vhvc3WP.html</ref>\nCurrently he is appearing as a Judge in [[Zee Punjabi]] \"Sa Re Ga Ma Pa\" with [[Sonu Kakkar]], [[Jaidev Kumar]] and show is mentoring by [[Gurdas Mann]].<ref>https://www.auditionform.in/news/zee-punjabi/zee-punjabi-sa-re-ga-ma-pa-start-date-2020-judges-host-contestants/</ref>\n\n==Fashion brand==\nB Jazzy is his fashion brand.<ref>http://www.jazzyb.com/?p=2520</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! Year \n! Album \n! Record label \n! No. of tracks \n! Music \n|-\n|2017\n| ''Folk 'N' Funky 2''\n| Zee Music Company\n| 12\n|rowspan='12'|Sukshinder Shinda\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''Maharajas''\n| MovieBox (UK)<br>Speed Records (India)<br>[[Music Waves]] (USA & Canada) \n| 12\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Rambo''\n| MovieBox (UK)<br>Speed Records (India)<br>Planet Recordz (USA & Canada)\n| 11\n|-\n| 2004\n|''[[Romeo (album)|Romeo]]''\n| MovieBox (UK)<br>[[Tips Industries Limited|Tips]] (India)<br>[[Music Waves]] (USA & Canada)\n| 10\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''Tera Roop''<ref name=roop>{{cite news | url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2002/20021030/cth2.htm#11 | title=Jazzy comes out with 'Tera Roop' | work=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]] | date=30 October 2002 | accessdate=18 February 2012}}</ref>\n| MovieBox (UK)<br>[[Tips Industries Limited|Tips]] (India)<br>[[Music Waves]] (USA & Canada) \n| 9\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Oh Kehri''\n| MovieBox (UK)<br>[[Music Waves]] (USA & Canada)<br>[[Tips Industries Limited|Tips]] (India)\n| 8\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''Stayin' Real''<br>''Surma''\n| Kiss Records<br>[[Music Waves]]<br>[[Tips Industries Limited|Tips]]\n| 9<br>8\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''All Eyez on Me''\n| Kiss Records<br>[[Music Waves]] \n| 9\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''Folkal Attraction''\n| Moviebox (UK)<br>SuperTone Melodies<br>[[Music Waves]] \n| 8\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''Folk 'N' Funky''\n| Moviebox (UK)<br>SuperTone Melodies<br>[[Music Waves]] \n| 8\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''The Canadian Spice''\n| SuperTone Melodies\n| 11\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''Ghugian Da Jorra''<ref name=roop/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kissrecords.com/new_releases_ghugian.html |title=New Releases |publisher=Kiss Records.com |date= |accessdate=31 January 2012}}</ref>\n| Moviebox (UK)<br>Kiss Records<br>Supe